## Guide to the preprocessed_data:
# excluded_participants lists the blocks based on which participants were excluded due to poor SART performance
#
#main_data is the data imported from qualtrics with exclusion. The data was used to get trial data and model dataset 
#
#model_dataset is block-level data including all information about participants
#
#model_dataset_overall does not have division into blocks, it contains: experimental duration, demographic variables, id, reaction time data including log-transformed rt, accuracy, percentage retained trials, inverse efficiency, all psychometric subscale scores and changes in energy, fatigue, accuracy and reaction time
#
#trial_data is all the trial data, including too short trials

#This part of the code was used to obtain numbers in groups

ages <- model_dataset_overall %>%
  mutate(age_group = ifelse(age < 30, 1, ifelse(age < 40, 2, ifelse( age < 50, 3, ifelse(age < 60, 4, ifelse(age < 70, 5, 6)))))) %>%
  group_by(age_group) %>%
  summarise(n = n())

nationality <- model_dataset_overall %>%
  group_by(tolower(nationality)) %>%
  summarise(n = n())

Log-correction

RTs

trial_data <- trial_data %>%
  filter(as.numeric(rt) >= 150) #omitting anticipation error

trial_data$rt <- log(as.numeric(trial_data$rt))

plot <- ggplot() +
  geom_area(aes(as.numeric(trial_data$rt)), stat="bin", binwidth = 0.01) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(as.numeric(na.omit(trial_data$rt))))) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(as.numeric(na.omit(trial_data$rt))) - sd(as.numeric(na.omit(trial_data$rt))))) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(as.numeric(na.omit(trial_data$rt))) + sd(as.numeric(na.omit(trial_data$rt)))))
plot

kurtosis(as.numeric(na.omit(trial_data$rt))) #slightly leptokurtic
## [1] 4.542313
skewness(as.numeric(na.omit(trial_data$rt))) #data is symmetrical after log transformation
## [1] 0.4963082

VAS change + MFI

Physical fatigue and reduced activation were related to reported changes in fatigue and energy, these were smaller with those present, not however when controlling for multiple comparisons for physical fatigue. They are also smaller in effect.
